---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Kinglet Programming Language">
<SiteHeader />

<main>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="shell hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Kinglet programming language</p>
        <h1>Native software,<br />with explicit boundaries.</h1>
        <p class="lede">Kinglet is a modern, statically typed language that compiles ahead of time to native code. Its C-family syntax stays familiar while ownership, exhaustive matching, and capability-oriented I/O make important program boundaries visible.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button" href="#get-started">Get Kinglet</a>
          <a class="text-link" href="/docs">Read the language guide <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="language" id="language">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <header class="section-intro">
        <p class="section-number">01 / Language</p>
        <h2>A small surface for systems that need to stay understandable.</h2>
        <p>Kinglet combines direct native compilation with language-level tools for expressing data, control flow, and resource access clearly.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="feature-list">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <div><h3>Ownership</h3><p>Resource lifetimes are part of the program model rather than hidden behind a tracing runtime.</p></div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <div><h3>Algebraic data types</h3><p>Enums carry data, and exhaustive pattern matching keeps every state accounted for.</p></div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <div><h3>Explicit capabilities</h3><p>Modules such as I/O and text encoding are imported and used at visible call sites.</p></div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>04</span>
          <div><h3>Native by default</h3><p>The compiler emits object code through LLVM and produces ordinary platform binaries.</p></div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="code-section" aria-labelledby="code-title">
    <div class="shell code-grid">
      <div class="code-copy">
        <p class="section-number section-number--light">02 / In code</p>
        <h2 id="code-title">Familiar syntax.<br />Stronger guarantees.</h2>
        <p>Tagged data and exhaustive matching are ordinary parts of the language—not framework conventions.</p>
        <a href="/docs">Explore Kinglet syntax <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <div class="editor" aria-label="Kinglet code example">
        <div class="editor-head"><span>shape.kl</span><span>kinglet</span></div>
<pre><code><span class="kw">using</span> io;

<span class="kw">enum</span> <span class="ty">Shape</span> {'{'}
  <span class="ty">Circle</span>(<span class="ty">float</span>),
  <span class="ty">Rect</span>(<span class="ty">float</span>, <span class="ty">float</span>),
{'}'}

<span class="ty">float</span> <span class="fn">area</span>(<span class="ty">Shape</span> shape) {'{'}
  <span class="kw">return</span> shape <span class="kw">match</span> {'{'}
    <span class="ty">Shape</span>::<span class="ty">Circle</span>(<span class="kw">let</span> r) ={'>'} <span class="num">3.14</span> * r * r,
    <span class="ty">Shape</span>::<span class="ty">Rect</span>(<span class="kw">let</span> w, <span class="kw">let</span> h) ={'>'} w * h,
  {'}'};
{'}'}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="compiler" id="compiler">
    <div class="shell section-grid">
      <header class="section-intro">
        <p class="section-number">03 / Toolchain</p>
        <h2>One compiler, from source to a native executable.</h2>
        <p>The C++ bootstrap compiler contains the parser, semantic checker, Kinglet IR, LLVM lowering, runtime, and command-line driver.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="pipeline" aria-label="Compilation pipeline">
        <div><strong>Source</strong><span>.kl</span></div><i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
        <div><strong>Check</strong><span>types + semantics</span></div><i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
        <div><strong>Lower</strong><span>Kinglet IR</span></div><i aria-hidden="true">→</i>
        <div><strong>Emit</strong><span>native code</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="project-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/kinglet-lang/bootstrap"><span>Compiler source</span><small>github.com/kinglet-lang/bootstrap</small></a>
        <a href="https://github.com/kinglet-lang/bootstrap/releases"><span>Releases</span><small>Prebuilt toolchains and release notes</small></a>
        <a href="https://github.com/kinglet-lang/ADRs"><span>Design decisions</span><small>Architecture decision records</small></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="get-started" id="get-started">
    <div class="shell start-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="section-number section-number--light">04 / Get started</p>
        <h2>Build your first Kinglet program.</h2>
        <p>Install the current toolchain, then follow the syntax guide to compile and run a source file.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="install-block">
        <div class="platform-tabs" role="group" aria-label="Installation platform">
          <button type="button" data-platform="macos" aria-pressed="true">macOS</button>
          <button type="button" data-platform="linux" aria-pressed="false">Linux</button>
          <button type="button" data-platform="windows" aria-pressed="false">Windows</button>
        </div>
        <div class="install-command"><span id="prompt">$</span><code id="cmd">curl -fsSL https://kinglet-lang.org/install.sh | sh</code><button id="copy" type="button"><span id="copy-label">copy</span></button></div>
        <div class="start-links"><a href="/docs">Open the language guide →</a><a href="https://github.com/kinglet-lang/bootstrap">Build from source →</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<SiteFooter />

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.platform-tabs button');
  var promptEl = document.getElementById('prompt');
  var cmdEl = document.getElementById('cmd');
  var copyBtn = document.getElementById('copy');
  var copyLabel = document.getElementById('copy-label');
  var commands = {
    macos: { prompt: '$', command: 'curl -fsSL https://kinglet-lang.org/install.sh | sh' },
    linux: { prompt: '$', command: 'curl -fsSL https://kinglet-lang.org/install.sh | sh' },
    windows: { prompt: 'PS>', command: 'irm https://kinglet-lang.org/install.ps1 | iex' }
  };
  var current = 'macos';
  function select(platform) {
    current = platform;
    promptEl.textContent = commands[platform].prompt;
    cmdEl.textContent = commands[platform].command;
    tabs.forEach(function (tab) { tab.setAttribute('aria-pressed', tab.dataset.platform === platform); });
  }
  var system = (navigator.userAgent || '') + (navigator.platform || '');
  select(/Win/i.test(system) ? 'windows' : /Linux/i.test(system) ? 'linux' : 'macos');
  tabs.forEach(function (tab) { tab.addEventListener('click', function () { select(tab.dataset.platform); }); });
  copyBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
    if (navigator.clipboard) navigator.clipboard.writeText(commands[current].command);
    copyLabel.textContent = 'copied';
    window.setTimeout(function () { copyLabel.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1400);
  });
})();
</script>
</BaseLayout>
